7 NEW SECTION. Section 4. Grants to increase access to early literacy targeted interventions.
8 (1) For the biennium beginning July 1, 2025, there is an early literacy targeted intervention boost grant program.
9 The purpose of the program is to support school districts in expanding access to the district's early literacy
10 targeted intervention classroom-based program without burdening local taxpayers. The office of public
11 instruction shall administer the program.
12 (2) Subject to and limited to the amount of legislative appropriation, when a school district
13 increases its ANB count under 20-9-313(1)(f), the office of public instruction shall distribute an early literacy
14 targeted intervention boost grant to the district in the amount of $1,000 for every ANB increased.
15 (3) A school district receiving a grant under this program shall:
16 (a) deposit the grant funding in the district's miscellaneous programs fund; and
17 (b) no later than June 30, 2027, expend the funding for any necessary classroom modifications or
18 curriculum purchases related to the expansion of the district's early literacy targeted intervention classroom
19 program.
20
21 NEW SECTION. Section 5. Appropriation. There is appropriated $2 million from the school facility
22 and technology account under 20-9-516 to the office of public instruction for the biennium beginning July 1,
23 2025, for the purpose of distributing grants to schools as described in [section 3].
